  "articleSummary": "**Summary:**  \nThe article argues that AI agents become truly useful only when integrated with business systems via standardized protocols like the Model Context Protocol (MCP), which solves the \"integration problem\" caused by fragmented, custom API wrappers. It positions MCP as a universal connector (framed as \"USB-C for AI tools\") that abstracts service-specific complexity, enabling agents to access tools like Salesforce or Google Maps without writing bespoke code. Targeting developers building multi-tool AI agents, the piece uses a tutorial tone with code examples from Mastra’s MCPClient to demonstrate setup, dynamic authentication, and composite tool creation. Recurring metaphors include \"hands and eyes\" for agents and \"cable drawers\" for legacy API fragmentation.",
